.TH HSH 1 "December 2022" "version 1.0" "HolbertonSchool-Simple_Shell"
.SH NAME
hsh - Simple Shell, basic command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IP Interactive Use:
  ./hsh $[command] [-options]
.IP Non-interactive Use:
  echo "[command] [-options]" | ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
The Holberton School Simple Shell (hsh) is a command language interpreter that executes commands read from a command line string. The application shall ensure that the commands will be executed or expressed on the standard output per the users input.

.SH BUILTINS
The following commands are builtin because they need to perform some operation that can't be performed by a separate process.

The builtin commands are:
.IP CTRL+D
Terminate the shell process.
.IP exit
Terminate the shell process.
.IP env
Display all environment variables.

.SH EXAMPLE
Execute simple shell commands and terminate the program.
  1) Open simple shell command line

    ./hsh

  2) Execute 'ls' command within simple shell

    ls -l

  3) Execute 'env' builtin command

    env

  4) Terminate the simple shell program

    exit

.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon succeful termination of the program, 0 is returned.

If an output error is encountered, the program will be terminated.
.SH BUGS
No known defects have been identified. To report any bugs, send an email to 5673@holbertonstudents.com or 5675@holbertonstudents.com
